&lt;h2 data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;54&quot;&gt;FPGA/Electronics Engineer – Quantum Computing Hardware&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;55&quot; data-end=&quot;192&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;55&quot; data-end=&quot;67&quot;&gt;Company:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;Quix Quantum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br data-start=&quot;105&quot; data-end=&quot;108&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;108&quot; data-end=&quot;121&quot;&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Netherlands&lt;br data-start=&quot;157&quot; data-end=&quot;160&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;160&quot; data-end=&quot;180&quot;&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;194&quot; data-end=&quot;197&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;716&quot; data-end=&quot;880&quot;&gt;We are seeking a talented and driven &lt;strong data-start=&quot;753&quot; data-end=&quot;777&quot;&gt;Electronics Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to contribute to the development of high-performance electronics for quantum computing applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;882&quot; data-end=&quot;1087&quot;&gt;In this role, you will design and implement FPGA-based systems, develop low-latency analog and digital circuits, and work with high-speed data interfaces that support our cutting-edge quantum processors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1089&quot; data-end=&quot;1237&quot;&gt;You will collaborate closely with physicists and software engineers to ensure seamless integration between control electronics and quantum hardware.&lt;/p&gt;
